comments.body:
@ricardobranco777 Thank you for the report. 
Looks like the scope of ipv6 addresses (fec0::) in the containers are **site** local, but we get the addr by selecting .scope=="**global**"  as https://github.com/)containers/podman/blob/e43216ed69b083d253711a5eaae123ccb988ea45/test/system/helpers.network.bash#L111, so we get null as the error in https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/26798#issuecomment-3179256933.
I didn't notice about that when I sent this PR, which was supposed to fix the ipv6 address order issue, but I can fix it together, just to wait some time for the kernel patch.
